25|$|Three years later, the U.S. Department of Labor settled {{its final}} civil case against Presser {{and the other}} Central States Pension Fund trustees. The agreement, which {{included}} Presser, turned operation of the pension fund over to a federal court until the year 2007. In addition, Presser and the other 17 trustees paid an additional $175,000 to reimburse the fund for certain other costs. It {{was the first time}} <b>the</b> <b>Labor</b> <b>Department</b> won restitution from individual pension fund trustees under the Employee Retirement Income Security Act (ERISA).|$|E
